data.chText: 通常的；寻常的；惯常的
data.enText: that happens or is done most of the time or in most cases

data.chText: 她净找了些司空见惯的借口。
data.enText: She made all the usual excuses.

data.chText: 他回家比平时晚了些。
data.enText: He came home later than usual.

data.chText: 她坐在后排平时惯坐的位子上。
data.enText: She sat in her usual seat at the back.

data.chText: 讲话前先感谢大家光临，这是惯例。
data.enText: It is usual to start a speech by thanking everybody for coming.

data.chText: 他听起来不像平常那个乐天派了。
data.enText: He didn't sound like his usual happy self.

data.chText: 惯常的事物；（尤指）常喝的饮料
data.enText: what usually happens; what you usually have, especially the drink that you usually have
as usual

data.chText: 照例；照旧；像往常一样
data.enText: in the same way as what happens most of the time or in most cases

data.chText: 史蒂夫照例来得最晚。
data.enText: Steve, as usual, was the last to arrive.

data.chText: 跟平常那个时刻一样，那地方空荡荡的。
data.enText: As usual at that hour, the place was deserted.

data.chText: 尽管她有困难，她照样继续工作。
data.enText: Despite her problems, she carried on working as usual.
business as usual

data.chText: （尽管处境困难）一切照常，不受干扰
data.enText: a way of saying that things will continue as normal despite a difficult situation
as per normal/usual

data.chText: 照常；按惯例；一如既往
data.enText: in the way that is normal or usual; as often happens

data.chText: 大家照例是责怪我。
data.enText: Everyone blamed me as per usual.

tr: occurring or encountered or experienced or observed frequently or in accordance with regular practice or procedure

value.def: Usual is used to describe what happens or what is done most often in a particular situation.

example.ex: It is a neighborhood beset by all the usual inner-city problems...
example.tran: 这是个为各种内城常见问题所困扰的社区。

example.ex: She's smiling her usual friendly smile...
example.tran: 她脸上挂着她一贯的微笑。

example.ex: After lunch there was a little more clearing up to do than usual...
example.tran: 午餐之后要做的清扫工作比平时略多。

example.ex: We've had more press coverage in the last three weeks than in the usual three years...
example.tran: 过去的三个星期里，媒体对我们的报道比往常的三年还多。

example.ex: It is usual to tip waiters, porters, guides and drivers.
example.tran: 给服务员、行李搬运工、导游和司机小费是惯例。

example.ex: The stout barman in a bow tie presented himself to take their order. 'Good morning, sir. The usual?'
example.tran: 那名打着领结的矮胖酒吧招待走上前来请他们点餐。“早上好，先生们。还是平常那些吗？”

gramarinfo.label: det ADJ, v-link ADJ, oft <l>it</l> v-link ADJ to-inf

value.def: You use as usual to indicate that you are describing something that normally happens or that is normally the case.

example.ex: As usual there will be the local and regional elections on June the twelfth...
example.tran: 照例，6月12日将会进行地方及区域选举。

example.ex: The front pages are, as usual, a mixture of domestic and foreign news.
example.tran: 像平常一样，头版上刊登着国内外新闻。

value.def: If something happens as usual, it happens in the way that it normally does, especially when other things have changed.

example.ex: When somebody died everything went on as usual, as if it had never happened...
example.tran: 就算有人死了一切也都照常进行，好像什么事都没发生过。

example.ex: With medication, life at home goes on as usual.
example.tran: 接受药物治疗后，家里的生活还能一切如常。

value.tran: （尤指其他事情有变化时）照常

trans: 像平常一样；照例；（尤指其他事情有变化时）照常

partsOfSpeech.dec: ab 相反 + use 用 → 反着用 → 滥用
ab 相反 + us 用 + ive …的，abuse的形容词 → 滥用的；谩骂的
dis 不 + abuse 滥用 → 不滥用 → 纠正错误
dis 不 + use 用 → 废弃；不用
mis 坏 + use 用 → 用的不对 → 错用
un 不 + usual 通常的 → 异乎寻常的
us 用 + age 表总称 → 用法；惯例
us 用 + ual 有…性质的 → 常用的 → 通常的
ut 用 + ensil 表物品 → 用的物品 → 用具
utilit〔y〕公用事业；有用 + arian …的 → 有用为主 → 功利主义的
util 用 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 公用事业；有用
util 用 + ize 使 → 利用
